                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*ZJKHbPjkNzbcmgnE7TM-Jg.jpeg"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;"><a href="https://www.aispacefactory.com/marsha" target="_self">https://www.aispacefactory.com/marsha</a></p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">3D printing is a great technology as it tries to automate house building. For now, we probably can print walls, but not really the whole house. We lack stability and reproducibility in that kind of build. For example, in a building process, we use concrete, and in needs to be fluid enough to poor through the nozzle, but it has to harden fast enough, so the next layer can be poured successfully. The consistency of the concrete depends on the temperature, humidity, and air pressure. Another problem is that building in different places means that we have different grounds to build on, which brings inconsistency in the process. Finally, there might be some anomalies during the build. And that’s all exactly why we need deep learning here.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Firstly, we can use temperature, humidity, air pressure sensors, and deep learning to adopt the needed compound, so we get the needed consistency of the concrete. Secondly, to work in different locations with anomalies and inconsistencies, we need to have a computer vision model, so our robot can analyze what’s it building.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">And finally, if we want to use this technology on other celestial bodies (<a href="https://www.aispacefactory.com/marsha" target="_self">like this example</a>), we need a maximum amount of automation and robustness, so we should use deep learning solutions.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Asteroid mining</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
