    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">As we have already discussed, we need as much automation as possible. That means that we are going to have a lot of things that could potentially break. It’s a good idea to monitor that and even better — to predict the breaking moment to prevent it.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Let’s say we have a motor with several sensors for monitoring. Using a deep learning algorithm, we can predict when our motor is going to break based on the data from sensors. That’s a pretty common task even here on Earth, and it is going to be handy elsewhere. This really is just an example; we can monitor a lot of different things, even with microphones or cameras.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
